## Linux Fundamentals

### User Management
| Command | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| whoami | Display current user |
| id | Show user ID and group IDs |
| sudo | Execute command as root |
| su - | Switch to root user |
| useradd username | Create new user |
| passwd username | Set user password |

Root user: Full system control (prompt #)
Normal user: Limited permissions (prompt $)

### Package Management (APT)
| Command | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| sudo apt update | Update package list |
| sudo apt upgrade -y | Upgrade all packages |
| sudo apt install package | Install package |
| sudo apt remove package | Remove package |
| apt search keyword | Search for package |

### File Operations
| Command | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| ls -la | List all files with details |
| cat file | Display file content |
| cp source dest | Copy file |
| mv source dest | Move/rename file |
| rm file | Delete file |
| mkdir dir | Create directory |
| chmod 755 file | Change permissions |

### Scripting Basics
#!/bin/bash

This is a comment
echo "Hello World"

Variables
NAME="John"
echo "My name is $NAME"

If statement
if [ "$NAME" = "John" ]; then
echo "It's John"
fi

Loop
for i in {1..5}; do
echo "Number $i"
done

text

### Operators, Piping, Redirection
| Operator | Meaning | Example |
|----------|---------|---------|
| && | Run if previous succeeded | mkdir test && cd test |
| || | Run if previous failed | cd dir || mkdir dir |
| | | Pipe output | ls | grep .txt |
| > | Redirect output (overwrite) | ls > files.txt |
| >> | Redirect output (append) | echo text >> file.txt |
| 2> | Redirect error | command 2> error.log |

### Ping Command
| Command | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| ping google.com | Continuous ping |
| ping -c 4 google.com | 4 packets only |
| ping -i 0.5 google.com | 0.5 second interval |

Output interpretation:
- icmp_seq: Sequence number (gaps indicate loss)
- ttl: Time To Live (remaining hops)
- time: Round trip time in milliseconds
